30|$|In fact, one {{district}} court in the First Circuit that has subsequently discussed the case concluded that “Cook is instructive, yet not dispositive, {{on the issue of}} morbid obesity as an ‘impairment.’” Nedder v. Rivier College, 908 F. Supp. 66, 75 n. 8 (D.N.H. 1995). See also Katz v. City Metal Co., 87 F. 3 d 26, 31 (1 st Cir. 1996); Mandel v. Boston Phoenix, Inc., 456 F. 3 d 198, 208 (1 st Cir. 2006) (citing Cook only in its discussions of <b>evidentiary</b> <b>burdens).</b>|$|R
